default4.3. default   defaultLack of protectiondefault for ldefaultandlord’s interests and financial stabilitydefault&#xa0;
default4.3.1. 
defaultWe feel that there is a common misconception that Landlords in the private rented sector are profiteering from housing benefit. 
defaultThis 
defaultis not the case. According to DCLG's most recent Landlord Survey from 2010
default, 
default79 per cent
default of all landlords earned less than a
default quarter of their income from letting properties in the private rented sector with 2
default1 per cent
