default4.5. default   defaultMonthly paymentsdefault&#xa0;
default4.5.1. 
defaultWe have concerns for tenants who could face budgetary challenges as all of their benefit payments are 
defaultcombined into one monthly sum
default. The long wait between payments and inexperience of 
defaultmoney management could have serious implications on both the landlord and the tenant.   This could lead to the tenant not allocating and saving enough money to pay the rent and getting into debt and rent arrears.  It is essential therefore that the local s
defaultervice framework which is intended to provide budgetary support for claimants is designed with the private sector in mind not just the social sector.
